{"id":"7814","name":"free-things-that-wed-pay-for-anyway-southern-festival-of-books","title":"Free Things That We&#x2019;d Pay For Anyway: Southern Festival Of Books","author":"Morgan Levy","date":"2011-10-14T13:00:00-05:00","tags":["freebies","southern festival of books"],"categories":["Culture &amp; Arts","Featured"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/urbanwoodchuck/4280165827/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4017/4280165827_af950debc6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></p><p>Today marks the start of the 23rd annual <a href=\"http://www.humanitiestennessee.org/programs/southern-festival-books/attend-festival\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.humanitiestennessee.org&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Southern Festival of Books</a>, a weekend of absolutely free panels, discussions and readings by both established and upcoming authors. We nerd out every year about the SFB, but even moreso this year &#x2013; We&#x2019;re a little book deprived in this city right about now. The <em>Nashville Scene</em> has pulled together a <a href=\"http://www.nashvillescene.com/nashville/day-by-day-highlights-of-2011s-southern-festival-of-books/Content?oid=2651161\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.nashvillescene.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">great list of highlights for each day</a>, and we recommend it as a starting point if the <a href=\"http://www.humanitiestennessee.org/programs/southern-festival-books/sessions\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.humanitiestennessee.org&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">straight up schedule</a> overwhelms you as much as it does us. The speaker lineup is punctuated by musical performances on the Cafe Stage and hands-on activities for kids on the Youth Stage. Whether you drop in for a session or camp out downtown for the entire weekend, be sure to take advantage of the SFB. We&#x2019;re blown away every year that an event of this caliber remains free to attend &#x2013; we&#x2019;d gladly pay for the privilege.</p><p><strong><a href=\"http://www.humanitiestennessee.org/programs/southern-festival-books/attend-festival\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.humanitiestennessee.org&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Southern Festival of Books</a>, October 14-16 at Legislative Plaza and the Tennessee Capitol Building in downtown Nashville. Friday 12-6pm, Saturday 9am-6pm, Sunday 12-5pm, free</strong>.</p><p><em>Photo by <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/urbanwoodchuck/4280165827/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">urbanwoodchuck</a>. </em></p><p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2009/10/09/southern-festival-of-books-a-literary-lineup-worth-seeing/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Southern Festival Of Books: A Literary Lineup Worth Seeing\">Southern Festival Of Books: A Literary Lineup Worth Seeing</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2009/05/01/beyond-elmington-park-the-tennessee-renaissance-festival/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Beyond Elmington Park: The Tennessee Renaissance Festival\">Beyond Elmington Park: The Tennessee Renaissance Festival</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2011/01/15/the-weekendist-free-free-free-edition/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: The Weekendist: Free! Free! Free! Edition\">The Weekendist: Free! Free! Free! Edition</a></li></ol></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}